@page "/3_bettercard"

<h1>Parameters and ChildContent</h1>

<p>
    Let's combine the last two examples and make a card component that allows only 1 header
</p>

<h4>TheCard source:</h4>
<pre>
&lt;div class="card"&gt;

    &lt;CardHeader&gt;@@HeaderText&lt;/CardHeader&gt;

    &lt;CardBody&gt;@@ChildContent&lt;/CardBody&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

@@code {

    [Parameter] 
    [EditorRequired]
    public string HeaderText { get; set; }

    [Parameter] public RenderFragment ChildContent { get; set; }

}    
</pre>


<h4>Code Sample:</h4>
<pre>
&lt;TheCard HeaderText="Blazor Hat"&gt;
    This is one of Fritz's hats
&lt;/TheCard&gt;
</pre> 

<TheCard HeaderText="Blazor Hat">
    This is one of <b>Fritz's</b> hats
    <br/>
    The Current Time is @DateTime.UtcNow
</TheCard>
